
Bibliography:

1. Adding bibliography to TeX-document with Zotero:
TeX document:
\usepackage[round,comma]{natbib}
\bibliographystyle{apalike}
\bibliography{biblio}
Use the extract BibTex (not BibLatex) to extract the bib file from Zotero.

2. Making non-standard characters order alphabetically in bibliography:
author = {{\'A}lvarez, Mar√≠a and ...}
See also here: https://tex.stackexchange.com/questions/57743/how-to-write-%C3%A4-and-other-umlauts-and-accented-letters-in-bibliography

3. Single name authors (use double braces):
author = {{Single name}}
